@kennknowles No, from [javadoc](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/reflect/Proxy.html#getProxyClass(java.lang.ClassLoader,%20java.lang.Class...)):

> All non-public interfaces must be in the same package; otherwise, it would not be possible for the proxy class to implement all of the interfaces, regardless of what package it is defined in.

We might be able to do something with ByteBuddy or ASM to remove this limitation but a significant rewrite of `PipelineOptionsFactory`/`ProxyInvocationHandler` would be required.
